{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_33","type":"agent_message","text":"Human intervention needed\n\nThe automated job failed for `org.apache.tika:tika-core:4.0.0-alpha-1`. Preserved work is available on the branch: https://github.com/oracle/graalvm-reachability-metadata/tree/ai%2Fvjovanov%2Fhuman-intervention%2Fissue-6774-fails-javac-compile-org.apache.tika-tika-core-4.0.0-alpha-1-b30b6de8\n\nThe original failing stage was `:compileTestJava` under `:tckTest`. In `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.tika:tika-core:4.0.0-alpha-1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-07T00-09-27-129997Z.log`, `RecursiveMetadataContentHandlerProxyAccess.java` fails because `RecursiveMetadataContentHandlerProxy` and `ForkServer` can no longer be resolved. An earlier compile attempt in `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.tika:tika-core:4.0.0-alpha-1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-07T00-06-05-985982Z.log` shows many more `cannot find symbol` errors across `ParamTest`, `AutoDetectParserFactoryTest`, `TikaConfig*`, `PipesServerTest`, and related tests, which points to broad upstream API changes in Tika 4.\n\nThe preserved branch eventually gets later Gradle runs green (`human-intervention-logs/org.apache.tika:tika-core:4.0.0-alpha-1/gradle-test/gradle-test-2026-06-07T00-20-55-519735Z.log`, `...00-21-14-298781Z.log`, `...00-21-31-525102Z.log`), but it does so by deleting 13 existing test sources and reducing the test suite from 19 Java test files on `3.3.0` to 6 on `4.0.0-alpha-1`. The preserved branch stats also show dynamic-access calls dropping from 115/126 in `stats/org.apache.tika/tika-core/3.3.0/stats.json` to 30/30 in `stats/org.apache.tika/tika-core/4.0.0-alpha-1/stats.json`, so this is not a safe compile-only repair. Native verification logs worth checking are `human-intervention-logs/org.apache.tika:tika-core:4.0.0-alpha-1/native-test-verify/cycle-15-runNativeTraceImage-2026-06-07T00-18-48-031107Z.log` through `cycle-18-runNativeTraceImage-2026-06-07T00-19-43-942382Z.log`, which show follow-on metadata work for missing `custom-mimetypes.xml`, `tika-example.nnmodel`, and Xerces reflection.\n\n1. Restore or replace the deleted config/parser/param/fork coverage with Tika 4-compatible tests instead of merging the preserved branch as-is.\n2. Re-run `compileTestJava`, `test`, and native verification for `-Pcoordinates=org.apache.tika:tika-core:4.0.0-alpha-1` after rebuilding the test suite.\n3. Re-check `stats/org.apache.tika/tika-core/4.0.0-alpha-1/stats.json` against `3.3.0` and only merge once dynamic-access coverage is back to an acceptable level."}}
